sentences: Laurence Cottle (born 16 December 1961) is a Welsh bass guitarist and composer.
He was a member of the fusion quartet The Fents and appeared on their second album, The Other Side, released on the Passport Jazz label in 1987.
In the 1990s, he produced three albums for guitarist Jim Mullen and recorded with British jazz musicians Mornington Lockett, Tim Garland, Django Bates, Gerard Presencer, and John Graham.
In 2000, Cottle appeared on the album Iommi from Tony Iommi.
From 2003 to 2006, he was a member of Bill Bruford's Earthworks.
In 2009, he produced albums for Claire Martin, Gareth Williams, and Mark Nightingale.
Cottle has also played on Eric Clapton's 1986 album August as well as Van Morrison's Keep Me Singing and Roll with the Punches.
